                            <comment id="14473198" author="melix" created="Tue, 21 Aug 2012 11:07:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem was that the type checker didn&apos;t use the real argument types in the second pass, but the argument types of the potential method. In that case, it tried to find a method &lt;tt&gt;List#add(Object)&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;List#add(String)&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
